Class GamePanel

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, java.util.EventListener, javax.accessibility.Accessible

    public class GamePanel
extends javax.swing.JPanel
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener
    Author:
    Tom Leibovich and Roee Shachar The gamePanel object is in practice the game itself. it holds the buttons matrix and calls the relevant MineButton methods. further more, it determines the state of the game, the mines left to clear and the timer.

        public GamePanel(int rows,
         int columns,
         int numberOfMines,

    • Method Detail

      • actionPerformed

        public void actionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent e)
        actionPerformed is called when the lose button calls it - every 1/50 second. it explodes or disables all buttons alternately right and left.
        Specified by:
        actionPerformed in interface java.awt.event.ActionListener

      • cellCleared

        public void cellCleared()
        this method is called when a cell is cleared. the field indicating how many cells are yet to clear is updated. if it equals zero then the user wins.

      • cheat

        public void cheat()
        this method is called when the Hint button is clicked. it reveals one mine and puts a flag on it.

      • explodeAll

        public void explodeAll()
        this method is called if the user loses. it calls the timer that explodes all the mines and disables all other cells.

      • falseFlag

        public void falseFlag(boolean b)
        this method is called if the player has put a flag on a cell with no mine or if he fixed his error.
        Parameters:
        b - indicates if the user flagged a non-mine or took the flag off.

      • flaggedMine

        public void flaggedMine()
        this method is called whenever a mine is flagged. it updates the relevant fields and if no mines are left victory scenario is called.

      • getButtons

        public MineButton[][] getButtons()
        getter for the button matrix
        Returns:
        button matrix

      • lose

        public void lose()
        lose scenario. the field is updated and the timer stops.

      • unFlaggedMine

        public void unFlaggedMine()
        this method is called whenever a mine is unflagged. the fields relevant to mines are updated.
